.\" Man page for Project 0x16. C - Simple Shell
.TH Simple Shell Manpage "12 August 2020" "version 1.0"
.SH NAME
.B simple_shell - Simple UNIX command interpreter

simple_shell - A shell is special user program which provide an interface to user to use operating system services.

It is a command language interpreter that execute commands read from input devices such as keyboards or from files.

.SH SYNOPSIS
The simple shell gets started when the user logs in or start the terminal.

./hsh
/bin/[command] [option]
[command] [option]

.SH DESCRIPTION
Shell can be accessed by user using a command line interface. A special program called Terminal in linux is provided to type in the human readable commands such as env, ls etc. and then it is being execute.

.SH EXAMPLE
$  /bin/ls -l
  -rw-r--r-- 1 root root     510 Aug 17 19:39 token.c
  -rwxr-xr-x 1 root root   17264 Aug 17 13:37 shell
  -rw-r--r-- 1 root root    1526 Aug 17 16:45 shell.c
  -rw-r--r-- 1 root root     615 Aug 18 11:37 simpleshell.h
  -rw-r--r-- 1 root root     728 Aug 14 18:50 match.c

$  ls -l
  -rw-r--r-- 1 root root     510 Aug 17 19:39 token.c
  -rwxr-xr-x 1 root root   17264 Aug 17 13:37 shell
  -rw-r--r-- 1 root root    1526 Aug 17 16:45 shell.c
  -rw-r--r-- 1 root root     615 Aug 18 11:37 simpleshell.h
  -rw-r--r-- 1 root root     728 Aug 14 18:50 match.c

$ /bin/pwd
  /root/simple_shell

$ hhhhh
  ./shell: No such file or directory

.SH BUILTIN COMMANDS

.SS env
- list the current environment variables

.SS exit
- exit the shell

